Class TryBlock

java.lang.Object
msvc.exceptions.TryBlock
All Implemented Interfaces:
ITryCatch
public class TryBlock extends Object implements ITryCatch
Represents a try block as implemented by MSVC.

    • setState

      public void setState(int state)
      'Sets' the state of this try block. Not to be used when constructing a try block; just set the right tryLow and tryHigh values through the constructor

      This function is called as part of determining the try/catch block layout of a function, and for a try block serves as a double-check that the correct state value has been determined.

      Specified by:
      setState in interface ITryCatch
      Parameters:
      state - The state to set.
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if state does not match tryLow.
